This paper discusses the legal personhood of AI and robots, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The survey conducted in the paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches upon the responsibility and liability of robots, which could be categorized under robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential risks and controversies surrounding the legal personhood of AI and robots, which could be classified under cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR).
